WHO IS HE, AND WHY ARE YOU
LETTING HIM MOVE IN?

11:38.965 --> 11:42.931
HIS NAME IS DEREK,
AND...DID YOU SEE HIM?

11:42.931 --> 11:44.965
STILL, I'M MISSING
SOMETHING.

11:44.965 --> 11:46.931
REMEMBER WHEN I TOLD YOU
I RAN INTO MY FIRST LOVE

11:46.931 --> 11:49.551
AT A PRINCE CONCERT
TWO WEEKS AGO?

11:49.551 --> 11:50.965
THAT WAS DEREK.

11:50.965 --> 11:53.344
HE'S HAD SOME BAD LUCK
RECENTLY,

11:53.344 --> 11:57.206
AND AS FATE WOULD HAVE IT,
I HAVE BEEN THERE TO HELP.

11:57.206 --> 12:00.275
NO WONDER YOU WERE LATE
THREE TIMES THIS WEEK.

12:00.275 --> 12:02.344
I'M SURPRISED
YOU MADE IT IN AT ALL.

12:02.344 --> 12:05.413
YEAH, WE'VE BEEN REKINDLING
OUR OLD FLAME.

12:05.413 --> 12:09.241
IT'S LIKE WE NEVER LOST TOUCH.
AND NOW WE CAN'T STOP TOUCHING.

12:09.241 --> 12:10.551
OH!

12:10.551 --> 12:13.482
THAT IS A GREAT STORY.
BUT STILL,

12:13.482 --> 12:16.275
MOVING IN TOGETHER
IS A REALLY BIG STEP.

12:16.275 --> 12:18.931
NOT TO MENTION, DON'T YOU
THINK IT'S KIND OF FAST?

12:20.206 --> 12:21.275
YEAH.

12:21.275 --> 12:24.586
BUT LOVE WON'T LET ME WAIT.

12:24.586 --> 12:26.689
WE'RE PICKING UP EXACTLY
WHERE WE LEFT OFF

12:26.689 --> 12:28.655
WHEN WE WERE 17.

12:28.655 --> 12:30.793
ABSOLUTELY NOTHING
HAS CHANGED.

12:30.793 --> 12:32.793
WE HAVE THE PERFECT
RELATIONSHIP.

12:32.793 --> 12:36.137
OH, OMAR...WHAT'S IT LIKE?

12:42.103 --> 12:43.413
MMM.

12:43.413 --> 12:44.965
[ GIGGLES ][ INHALES SHARPLY ]

12:44.965 --> 12:46.862
I COULD EASILY GET USED
TO THIS EVERY NIGHT.

12:46.862 --> 12:49.206
REALLY? WHY?

12:49.206 --> 12:52.310
BECAUSE YOU'RE A VERY
SPECIAL LADY,

12:52.310 --> 12:54.206
AND YOU MAKE ME SO HAPPY.

12:54.206 --> 12:56.758
I KNOW IT MAY SEEM
A LITTLE SOON

12:56.758 --> 12:59.103
TO TALK ABOUT OUR FUTURE,
BUT WHEN I SAW YOU

12:59.103 --> 13:01.241
THIS MORNING IN THAT
WEDDING DRESS, I THOUGHT,

13:01.241 --> 13:03.482
"NOW'S AS GOOD A TIME
AS ANY."

13:03.482 --> 13:06.724
[ LAUGHS ] WOW.

13:06.724 --> 13:08.172
OKAY.

13:09.517 --> 13:11.172
WOW.

13:11.172 --> 13:12.965
VALERIE...

13:12.965 --> 13:16.310
I'M FALLING FOR YOU.

13:16.310 --> 13:19.965
AND I DON'T KNOW IF YOU'RE
QUITE THERE YET, BUT...

13:19.965 --> 13:21.965
I'M CERTAIN.

13:21.965 --> 13:24.000
I DON'T WANT TO GROW OLD
WITHOUT YOU.

13:24.000 --> 13:27.862
JERRY, I'M FALLING
FOR YOU, TOO.

13:27.862 --> 13:32.068
I COULDN'T ASK FOR A MORE
WONDERFUL MAN.

13:32.068 --> 13:35.000
I FEEL LIKE THE LUCKIEST
GIRL IN THE WORLD.

13:35.000 --> 13:37.793
I'M SO GLAD YOU FEEL
THAT WAY.

13:42.862 --> 13:44.482
NOW...

13:44.482 --> 13:46.068
[ BREATHES SHARPLY ]

13:46.068 --> 13:48.896
I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT THIS
LONG AND HARD.

13:49.896 --> 13:51.586
AND I NEED TO SHARE WITH YOU

13:51.586 --> 13:53.413
A DECISION I MADE
A FEW YEARS AGO

13:53.413 --> 13:56.068
ABOUT MARRIAGE, KIDS.

13:56.068 --> 13:58.827
I ONLY BRING THIS UP NOW
BECAUSE

13:58.827 --> 14:00.862
EARLIER, I SAW THAT LOOK
IN YOUR EYE

14:00.862 --> 14:03.103
THAT SAID YOU REALLY WANT
TO GET MARRIED ONE DAY.

14:04.448 --> 14:05.931
YEAH. OF --

14:05.931 --> 14:09.758
NOT TODAY OR ANYTHING, BUT...
[ LAUGHS ]

14:09.758 --> 14:11.482
YES, EVENTUALLY.

14:11.482 --> 14:15.068
WELL, I'VE BEEN MARRIED
THREE TIMES.

14:16.931 --> 14:20.551
BUT I'VE ALSO BEEN DIVORCED
THREE TIMES.

14:20.551 --> 14:23.620
AFTER THE LAST ONE,
I DECIDED...

14:23.620 --> 14:28.172
I COULDN'T ENDURE ANOTHER
UNHAPPY ENDING.

14:28.172 --> 14:30.931
AND SINCE I ALREADY HAVE
FOUR CHILDREN,

14:30.931 --> 14:33.827
I THINK I'M DONE
IN THAT AREA AS WELL.

14:33.827 --> 14:37.172
NOW I KNOW YOU'RE GOING
IN YOUR MIND, BUT HEAR ME OUT.

14:37.172 --> 14:42.000
IF YOU ARE WILLING
TO SHARE YOUR LIFE WITH ME,

14:42.000 --> 14:45.551
I'D LOVE TO SHARE MINE
WITH YOU FOREVER.

14:46.689 --> 14:49.931
I PROMISE TO ALWAYS
LOVE YOU,

14:49.931 --> 14:52.137
AND TO BE TRUE TO YOU.

14:52.137 --> 14:55.965
I JUST...DON'T WANT
TO GET MARRIED AGAIN --

14:55.965 --> 14:58.344
TO ANYONE...EVER.

15:04.344 --> 15:05.965
TALK TO ME, VALERIE.

15:07.896 --> 15:09.551
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

15:09.551 --> 15:11.620
IS THIS A DEAL-BREAKER?

15:15.517 --> 15:18.103
I... [ CLEARS THROAT ]

15:18.103 --> 15:19.655
I DON'T KNOW.

15:19.655 --> 15:21.655
[ BREATH SHUDDERS ]

15:21.655 --> 15:25.758
IT'S A LOT TO DIGEST.

15:25.758 --> 15:28.758
I'M GONNA NEED SOME TIME
TO THINK ABOUT IT.

15:28.758 --> 15:32.758
YOU TAKE ALL THE TIME
YOU NEED.

15:32.758 --> 15:34.379
I'LL BE HERE.

15:34.379 --> 15:36.379
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:39.482 --> 15:41.517
[ BREATHES UNEVENLY ]

15:41.517 --> 15:44.103
I GUESS I BETTER CLEAR
THE TABLE.

15:55.241 --> 15:57.517
[ PLATES CLATTER ]

16:02.034 --> 16:04.137
I AM CONVINCED

16:04.137 --> 16:06.931
THAT THERE ARE FORCES
IN THE UNIVERSE

16:06.931 --> 16:09.689
THAT ARE CONSPIRING TO ROB ME
OF MY MOMENT.

16:09.689 --> 16:12.551
I AM NOT GONNA LET IT HAPPEN.

16:12.551 --> 16:14.000
I GET THAT YOU WEREN'T
EXPECTING THIS,

16:14.000 --> 16:16.482
BUT, REALLY, WHY ARE YOU
SO UPSET?

16:16.482 --> 16:20.931
WHY AM I UPSET? I FINALLY
MEET THE PERFECT GUY --

16:20.931 --> 16:24.482
SMART, GENEROUS,
TREATS ME LIKE A QUEEN --

16:25.896 --> 16:29.724
BUT HIS IDEA OF A BIG PROPOSAL
IS TO NEVER PROPOSE?

16:29.724 --> 16:31.482
IT'S A CONSPIRACY.

16:31.482 --> 16:33.689
NO, THE CONSPIRACY
IS IN THE IDEA

16:33.689 --> 16:35.689
THAT MARRIAGE IS THE BE-ALL
AND END-ALL

16:35.689 --> 16:38.000
OF EVERY RELATIONSHIP.
IT'S NOT.

16:38.000 --> 16:40.655
YEAH. YOU'RE PUTTING
WAY TOO MUCH EMPHASIS

16:40.655 --> 16:42.413
ON THE FANTASY OF MARRIAGE

16:42.413 --> 16:45.000
AND NOT ENOUGH ON THE FACT
THAT HE'S OFFERING YOU

16:45.000 --> 16:47.206
THE "HAPPILY EVER AFTER."

16:47.206 --> 16:50.103
BUT ISN'T THAT LIKE
GOING TO THE OLYMPICS

16:50.103 --> 16:52.620
AND SAYING YOU DON'T CARE
IF YOU MEDAL?

16:52.620 --> 16:55.344
MARRIAGE IS THE PINNACLE
OF DATING.

16:55.344 --> 16:57.344
IT'S RELATIONSHIP GOLD.

16:57.344 --> 17:00.310
MARRIAGE IS FOOL'S GOLD.

17:00.310 --> 17:01.448
AND IF YOU WANT MY TWO CENTS,

17:01.448 --> 17:03.241
YOU ALREADY HAVE GOLD
WITH JERRY.

17:03.241 --> 17:05.344
SHE'S RIGHT, VAL.
PEOPLE HAVE BIG,

17:05.344 --> 17:08.103
BEAUTIFUL, LAVISH CEREMONIES
ALL THE TIME...

17:08.103 --> 17:11.310
AND END UP MISERABLE
AS SOON AS EVERYONE GOES HOME.

17:11.310 --> 17:13.137
OH, COME ON, KEISHA.

17:13.137 --> 17:15.137
ARE YOU SAYING YOU DON'T
WANT TO MARRY MALCOLM?

17:15.137 --> 17:18.586
I'M SAYING I DON'T HAVE
A PROBLEM IF HE NEVER ASKS.

17:18.586 --> 17:20.689
I'M JUST HAPPY
BEING WITH HIM.

17:20.689 --> 17:24.275
SO WHATEVER FORM
THAT COMMITMENT TAKES

17:24.275 --> 17:25.620
IS COOL WITH ME.

17:25.620 --> 17:27.413
I DON'T NEED A WEDDING
FOR THAT.

17:27.413 --> 17:31.275
YOU SEEM TO BE FORGETTING
THE SMALL ISSUE

17:31.275 --> 17:33.310
OF ME WANTING
TO HAVE CHILDREN.

17:33.310 --> 17:34.620
GIRL, PLEASE.

17:34.620 --> 17:37.862
IF YOU WANT A BABY WITH JERRY,
YOU CAN GET A BABY.

17:37.862 --> 17:39.862
MAYBE.

17:39.862 --> 17:42.413
BUT I DON'T JUST WANT
A BABY.

17:42.413 --> 17:44.103
I'VE BEEN DREAMING ABOUT
GETTING MARRIED

17:44.103 --> 17:45.655
SINCE I WAS 6 YEARS OLD.

17:45.655 --> 17:46.965
I HAD THAT SAME DREAM.

17:46.965 --> 17:49.068
BUT I CAN TELL YOU
FIRST-HAND --

17:49.068 --> 17:50.827
DIVORCE IS HELL.

17:50.827 --> 17:54.344
I'M NOT SURE IF I EVER
WANT TO GET MARRIED AGAIN.

17:54.344 --> 17:56.034
MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

17:56.034 --> 17:58.241
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

17:58.241 --> 18:01.413
MAYBE I AM JUST TOO
CAUGHT UP IN AN IDEA.

18:01.413 --> 18:03.275
NOW YOU'RE THINKING.

18:03.275 --> 18:05.586
PLUS, IF YOU DON'T GET MARRIED,

18:05.586 --> 18:08.724
ME AND APRIL WON'T HAVE TO WEAR
UGLY BRIDESMAID DRESSES.

18:08.724 --> 18:11.275
WHO WANTS MORE WINE?

18:11.275 --> 18:13.793
OOH, OOH, ME.[ LAUGHING ] I DO.

18:13.793 --> 18:17.206
I KNOW YOU DO.[ LAUGHS ] YEAH.

18:17.206 --> 18:18.655
THEN YOU BETTER RUN
TO THE STORE,

18:18.655 --> 18:21.655
BECAUSE I'M KILLING
THE REST OF THIS.

18:21.655 --> 18:25.034
[ INHALES, EXHALES SHARPLY ]

18:25.034 --> 18:28.931
Woman:
♪ ANOTHER DAY IS DONE ♪

18:28.931 --> 18:31.241
♪ AND YOU'RE STILL
THE ONLY ONE ♪

18:31.241 --> 18:33.103
[ SIGHS ]♪ FOR ME ♪

18:33.103 --> 18:35.517
SORRY I'M SO LATE.
VAL REALLY NEEDED TO TALK.

18:35.517 --> 18:37.241
EVERYTHING OKAY?

18:37.241 --> 18:39.827
MM-HMM. I HOPE SO.

18:39.827 --> 18:41.103
HMM.

18:41.103 --> 18:44.586
SO HOW DID YOUR, UH,
YOUR MEETING GO TODAY?

18:44.586 --> 18:46.965
DID YOU GET THE LISTING?I SHOWED UP
LOOKING LIKE THIS,

18:46.965 --> 18:48.517
AND THEN I WAS ME.

18:48.517 --> 18:50.310
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

18:50.310 --> 18:52.482
UH, CONGRATULATIONS.

18:52.482 --> 18:55.655
THANK YOU.ALL RIGHT, NOW LISTEN, BABE.

18:55.655 --> 18:58.172
I KNOW YOU MUST HAVE SOME
QUESTIONS ABOUT EARLIER,

18:58.172 --> 19:00.344
BUT FOR STARTERS,
I HAD NO CLUE

19:00.344 --> 19:02.482
ASHLEE WAS COMING BY
THIS MORNING.

19:02.482 --> 19:04.482
MALCOLM, I'M SO NOT WORRIED
ABOUT THAT.

19:04.482 --> 19:06.379
I DON'T WANT
TO CHECK UP ON YOU,

19:06.379 --> 19:08.379
AND THERE'S
NO NEED TO EXPLAIN.

19:08.379 --> 19:09.827
I TRUST YOU.

19:16.206 --> 19:18.620
BUT SINCE YOU
BROUGHT IT UP...

19:22.344 --> 19:24.103
I KNEW THAT WAS TOO EASY.

19:24.103 --> 19:27.586
MM...IF IT HELPS,
MY PLAN WAS TO LET IT GO.

19:27.586 --> 19:30.965
BUT SINCE SHE CAN'T SEEM
TO LET YOUGO...

19:30.965 --> 19:32.758
LET'S HEAR IT.

19:32.758 --> 19:34.137
OKAY.

19:34.137 --> 19:35.793
YOU ALREADY KNOW THAT
ASHLEE AND I

19:35.793 --> 19:37.965
STARTED DATING
BACK IN BUSINESS SCHOOL.

19:37.965 --> 19:40.517
BUT AFTER A FEW MONTHS,
SHE WANTED TO GET MARRIED.

19:40.517 --> 19:42.724
I DIDN'T FEEL THE SAME WAY,
SO I BROKE IT OFF.

19:42.724 --> 19:44.724
BUT SHE WORKED HER WAY
BACK IN.

19:44.724 --> 19:46.137
IN A SENSE.

19:47.413 --> 19:50.000
YOU SEE, I KNEW MY POPS
NEEDED CAPITAL

19:50.000 --> 19:52.206
TO COMPETE WITH THE JACOBS
OF THE JEWELRY WORLD.

19:52.206 --> 19:55.379
NO ONE WAS BUYING HIS LITTLE
CLASSIC PIECES ANYMORE.

19:55.379 --> 19:57.103
THEY WANTED BIG BLING.

19:57.103 --> 19:59.103
WHAT DOES THIS HAVE TO DO
WITH ASHLEE?

19:59.103 --> 20:02.172
I MET WITH A LOT OF INVESTORS,
BUT THEY ALL FELL THROUGH.

20:02.172 --> 20:04.551
SO FINALLY I ASKED ASHLEE

20:04.551 --> 20:06.689
IF SHE WOULD GET HER FATHER
TO GIVE ME A LOAN.

20:06.689 --> 20:08.310
HE GOT MONEY LIKE THAT?

20:08.310 --> 20:09.931
LIKE YOU WOULDN'T BELIEVE.

20:09.931 --> 20:12.172
HE WAS BIG-TIME
IN THE SHIPPING INDUSTRY.

20:12.172 --> 20:15.896
DUDE HAD A GAZILLION DOLLARS
AT THE TIME.

20:15.896 --> 20:18.620
SO DID SHE GET IT
FOR YOU?

20:18.620 --> 20:20.827
SHE SAID SHE WOULD.

20:20.827 --> 20:22.379
BUT ONLY IF I MARRIED HER.

20:22.379 --> 20:25.517
DAMN. SHE WANTED YOU BAD.

20:25.517 --> 20:27.689
AND I FIGURED,
WHAT THE HELL?

20:27.689 --> 20:29.724
I MEAN, THERE WERE WORSE
THINGS THAT I COULD DO

20:29.724 --> 20:31.172
TO HELP OUT MY POPS.

20:31.172 --> 20:35.344
SO I-I BASICALLY USED HER
TO EXPAND FRANKS JEWELS.

20:35.344 --> 20:37.448
AND EVEN THOUGH I PAID
HER FATHER BACK,

20:37.448 --> 20:39.620
HER FAMILY NEVER FORGAVE HER
FOR MARRYING

20:39.620 --> 20:41.103
A LOW-CLASS BLACK MAN.

20:41.103 --> 20:42.931
HE DIDN'T KNOW YOU TWO
WERE DATING

20:42.931 --> 20:44.379
WHEN HE GAVE YOU THE LOAN?

20:44.379 --> 20:46.620
NO, HE THOUGHT I WAS
JUST A FRIEND.

20:46.620 --> 20:48.241
WHOA.

20:48.241 --> 20:49.793
HAVE THEY FORGIVEN HER NOW?

20:49.793 --> 20:51.620
NO.

20:51.620 --> 20:53.931
THEY WILL NEVER FORGIVE HER.

20:53.931 --> 20:57.689
SO I-I CHECK UP ON HER
A FEW TIMES A YEAR

20:57.689 --> 20:59.862
JUST TO SEE
HOW SHE'S DOING.

20:59.862 --> 21:01.413
IT'S THE LEAST I CAN DO,
RIGHT?

21:01.413 --> 21:02.862
WELL, DAMN.

21:06.758 --> 21:08.517
THANK YOU FOR BEING
HONEST WITH ME.

21:09.827 --> 21:12.206
MM.[ CHUCKLES ]

21:12.206 --> 21:13.551
HONEST? [ CHUCKLES ]

21:13.551 --> 21:16.379
I DON'T KNOW THAT,
MALCOLM.

21:16.379 --> 21:18.413
WHAT'S UP, KEISHA?

21:18.413 --> 21:21.103
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE WHOLE
BRUNCH THING A FEW WEEKS AGO.

21:21.103 --> 21:23.275
I DIDN'T MEAN NO HARM.

21:23.275 --> 21:25.241
NO WORRIES, TERRENCE.
WE'RE ALL GOOD.

21:25.241 --> 21:26.448
YOU'RE LATE.

21:26.448 --> 21:29.379
I TOLD YOU TO BE HERE
TWO HOURS AGO.

21:29.379 --> 21:30.896
AND THAT'S WHERE YOU
KEEP MESSING UP.

21:30.896 --> 21:34.482
THINKING THAT YOU CAN TELL ME
WHAT TO DO AND WHERE TO BE.

21:34.482 --> 21:37.931
LAST I CHECKED,
YOUR NAME WASN'T DADDY.

21:37.931 --> 21:39.379
WELL, MAYBE TO HER.

21:42.793 --> 21:44.482
I'M-A LET YOU GUYS TALK.

21:50.896 --> 21:52.689
DAMN.

21:52.689 --> 21:55.103
SHE IS FINE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:55.103 --> 21:57.620
[ INHALES AND SIGHS ]
I'M HERE. WHAT DO YOU WANT?

22:01.931 --> 22:03.413
[ SIGHS ]

22:05.724 --> 22:08.758
HEY, YOU KNOW SOMETHING?
I WANT A COUPLE OF THINGS.

22:08.758 --> 22:12.172
FIRST, YOU AND YOUR BOYS

22:12.172 --> 22:13.896
NEED TO FIND A NEW PLACE
TO HANG OUT

22:13.896 --> 22:15.896
THAT'S NOWHERE NEAR
ASHLEE'S SALON.

22:15.896 --> 22:20.344
AND SECOND, I GAVE YOU A JOB
AND AN OFFICE NEXT TO MINE.

22:20.344 --> 22:21.896
NOW WHY DON'T YOU
STOP HUSTLING,

22:21.896 --> 22:24.310
BE A MAN ABOUT IT,
AND SHOW UP?

22:24.310 --> 22:27.068
I'M NOT ABOUT TO STAND HERE
AND LET YOU QUESTION MY MANHOOD.

22:27.068 --> 22:29.793
TERRENCE, I'M NOT TRYING
TO DISRESPECT YOU,

22:29.793 --> 22:31.379
BUT I AM TRYING TO SHOW YOU

22:31.379 --> 22:33.413
YOU DON'T HAVE TO LIVE
THIS LIFE ANYMORE.

22:33.413 --> 22:35.206
THIS IS THE ONLY LIFE
THAT I KNOW.

22:35.206 --> 22:37.965
SO IF YOU WANT ME
OUT OF ASHLEE'S SALON,

22:37.965 --> 22:40.068
FORGET ABOUT THE JOB
AND THE OFFICE,

22:40.068 --> 22:42.103
AND BUY ME
OUT OF THE COMPANY.

22:42.103 --> 22:44.620
GIVE ME MY MONEY.

22:44.620 --> 22:46.551
THEN I'LL BE GONE.

22:46.551 --> 22:48.965
THAT...

22:48.965 --> 22:50.517
IS NEVER GONNA HAPPEN.

22:51.620 --> 22:54.655
I HATE YOU RIGHT NOW, DUDE.

22:54.655 --> 22:56.827
GROW UP, TERRENCE.

23:06.137 --> 23:07.827
WATCH YOUR BACK WITH HIM.

23:07.827 --> 23:09.655
EVERYTHING AIN'T
WHAT IT SEEMS --

23:09.655 --> 23:12.310
STARTING WITH ASHLEE.

23:12.310 --> 23:15.931
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

23:18.517 --> 23:21.137
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

23:22.586 --> 23:26.137
YOU KNOW, IT'S GETTING
PRETTY HOT IN HERE.

23:26.137 --> 23:28.000
HMM, THAT'S PRETTY HOT.

23:28.000 --> 23:29.724
THAT IS NICE.

23:29.724 --> 23:34.206
WELL,
I THINK YOUR HAIR IS NICE.

23:34.206 --> 23:36.103
AND I THINK YOURS
IS PRETTY SEXY, TOO.

23:36.103 --> 23:38.827
YEAH, I LOVE IT.
IT'S SO CUTE.

23:38.827 --> 23:39.931
OH, MY GOD.

23:39.931 --> 23:40.931
I TOTALLY LIKE YOURS.

23:40.931 --> 23:42.620
YOU KNOW, THE GIRL
YOU CUTS MY HAIR

23:42.620 --> 23:44.413
TOLD ME THAT IF I BROUGHT IN
A FRIEND,

23:44.413 --> 23:45.655
WE COULD BOTH GET HALF OFF.

23:45.655 --> 23:47.586
THAT IS SO COOL.
UM, WHAT'S YOUR NUMBER?

23:47.586 --> 23:48.689
DO YOU WANNA BUMP IT?

23:48.689 --> 23:50.482
OH, YEAH. I JUST DOWNLOADED
THAT APP.

23:50.482 --> 23:52.413
OKAY, THAT'S NOT THE KIND
OF BUMPING

23:52.413 --> 23:54.758
THAT'S SUPPOSED TO BE GOING DOWN
HERE TONIGHT.

23:54.758 --> 23:58.620
OKAY? SO NO MORE HAIR TALK.

23:58.620 --> 24:01.482
WE ALL KNOW WHAT WE'RE HERE FOR.

24:01.482 --> 24:03.448
♪♪♪

24:03.448 --> 24:04.793
LET'S GET IT STARTED.

24:04.793 --> 24:07.310
♪♪♪

24:07.310 --> 24:09.344
OKAY,
I WANNA SEE YOU GUYS KISS.

24:09.344 --> 24:12.689
♪♪♪

24:12.689 --> 24:14.689
[ KISS ]

24:14.689 --> 24:18.344
OKAY. NICE. NICE.

24:18.344 --> 24:27.482
♪♪♪

24:30.448 --> 24:32.034
[ EXHALES ]

24:32.034 --> 24:33.965
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

24:33.965 --> 24:36.137
[ EXHALES ]

24:36.137 --> 24:37.689
[ BOTH LAUGHING ]

24:37.689 --> 24:39.689
OKAY, UH, STOP.
YOU KNOW WHAT? FORGET IT.

24:39.689 --> 24:41.827
I DON'T...I DON'T NEED TO TAKE
MY PANTS OFF TO MAKE THIS WORK.

24:41.827 --> 24:44.068
[ GIGGLES ]

24:44.068 --> 24:47.896
♪♪♪

24:53.448 --> 24:54.724
UM...

24:59.344 --> 25:01.620
Woman: ♪ WHAT'S ♪

25:01.620 --> 25:04.862
♪ THE MATTER ♪

25:04.862 --> 25:07.793
♪ WITH YOU? ♪

25:07.793 --> 25:10.000
♪ AND YOU SAY ♪

25:10.000 --> 25:12.344
♪ WHAT'S ♪

25:12.344 --> 25:13.586
♪ THE MATTER ♪

25:13.586 --> 25:15.137
[ SCOFFS ]

25:15.137 --> 25:18.137
♪ WITH ME? ♪

25:18.137 --> 25:21.137
♪ I SAY ♪

25:21.137 --> 25:22.379
♪ WHAT'S ♪

25:22.379 --> 25:25.068
I'LL GO, UM...
GRAB SOME MORE BEER.

25:25.068 --> 25:27.344
♪ WITH YOU ♪

25:27.344 --> 25:31.000
♪ I SAY ♪

25:31.000 --> 25:34.931
♪ I'M NOT COMING, I'M NOT ♪

25:37.655 --> 25:39.827
♪♪♪

25:39.827 --> 25:42.137
YO, BRING DOWN THE BASS ON THAT
CHANGE TO THE CHORUS, MAN.

25:42.137 --> 25:44.862
I NEED TO FEEL IT IN MY CHEST,
NOT MY THROAT.

25:44.862 --> 25:47.310
OKAY, COOL, COOL.
RIGHT THERE.

25:47.310 --> 25:50.379
♪♪♪

25:50.379 --> 25:51.965
ALL RIGHT, UM, TAKE FIVE,

25:51.965 --> 25:53.965
AND THEN WE'LL WORK ON THAT
GUITAR SPOT ON THE BRIDGE.

25:53.965 --> 25:56.448
SOUNDS GREAT, REED.

25:56.448 --> 25:58.551
THANKS. THAT'S WHY
I CAN'T FIGURE OUT

25:58.551 --> 26:01.482
WHY WES ISN'T DOWN HERE
OFFERING ME A FAT, NEW CONTRACT

26:01.482 --> 26:02.482
RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

26:02.482 --> 26:03.655
YOU KNOW THAT HE WANTS ME
TO GET YOU

26:03.655 --> 26:04.827
TO SIGN A 360 DEAL,
RIGHT?

26:04.827 --> 26:06.655
A 360?!

26:06.655 --> 26:08.103
UN-FREAKING-BELIEVABLE!

26:08.103 --> 26:10.000
WHO DOES HE THINK I AM,
SOME CLUELESS KID

26:10.000 --> 26:12.344
POSTING SONGS ON YouTube?

26:12.344 --> 26:13.931
I KNEW THAT YOU'D REFUSE,

26:13.931 --> 26:16.000
BUT I'M SURE
WE CAN NEGOTIATE.

26:16.000 --> 26:17.068
WHY WOULD I NEGOTIATE

26:17.068 --> 26:18.241
WITH SOMEONE
WHO THINKS SO LITTLE OF ME?

26:18.241 --> 26:19.517
BECAUSE THE ONLY THING

26:19.517 --> 26:21.931
THAT WES HATES MORE THAN
LOSING MONEY ON A NEW ARTIST

26:21.931 --> 26:23.379
IS WATCHING SOMEONE ELSE
MAKE MONEY ON ITS OLD ARTIST.

26:23.379 --> 26:24.724
IT MAY TAKE A MINUTE,

26:24.724 --> 26:28.448
BUT EVERYONE WILL END UP
HAPPY ON THIS.

26:28.448 --> 26:30.275
YOU KNOW,
ANY OTHER LABEL HEAD

26:30.275 --> 26:32.275
WOULD BE KISSING MY ASS
RIGHT NOW,

26:32.275 --> 26:34.517
NOT SENDING THEIR ASSISTANT
TO DO IT.

26:36.689 --> 26:39.620
SO...ALL THE BLOOD,
SWEAT, AND TEARS

26:39.620 --> 26:41.965
THAT I'VE PUT
INTO YOUR CAREER,

26:41.965 --> 26:43.724
AND YOU'RE TELLING ME
THAT YOU STILL SEE ME

26:43.724 --> 26:45.034
AS JUST AN ASSISTANT?

26:45.034 --> 26:47.000
REED, PLEASE DON'T START
PULLING OUT THE CRAZY ON ME,

26:47.000 --> 26:48.000
NOT THIS SOON.

26:48.000 --> 26:49.724
LOOK, I DIDN'T MEAN IT
THAT WAY,

26:49.724 --> 26:52.034
BUT SERIOUSLY, I CAN'T THINK
OF ONE GOOD REASON

26:52.034 --> 26:53.586
WHY I SHOULD STAY
AT BIG MIX.

26:53.586 --> 26:54.965
I CAN.

26:54.965 --> 26:56.137
ME.

26:56.137 --> 26:58.344
YOU CAN'T DENY
THAT WE WORK WELL TOGETHER.

26:58.344 --> 26:59.896
LOOK AT WHERE YOU ARE NOW.

26:59.896 --> 27:02.034
YEAH, APRIL,
LOOK WHERE IAM NOW.

27:02.034 --> 27:04.344
IT'S ME AND MY TALENT
THAT GOT ME HERE.

27:04.344 --> 27:06.758
IT'S ME PEOPLE BOUGHT TICKETS
TO SEE TONIGHT,

27:06.758 --> 27:08.344
NOT YOU, NOT WES,
NOT NOBODY ELSE.

27:08.344 --> 27:10.586
WELL, IT WASN'T WES
AND NOBODY ELSE

27:10.586 --> 27:13.034
WHO TOOK CARE OF YOU
WHEN YOU OVERDOSED.

27:13.034 --> 27:15.310
NOBODY ELSE HOOKED YOU UP
WITH SUPERTRACKS

27:15.310 --> 27:16.551
OR PUSHED YOU UNTIL YOU

27:16.551 --> 27:18.241
ACTUALLY WROTE SOMETHING GOOD,
REED!

27:18.241 --> 27:19.482
THAT WAS ALL ME.

27:19.482 --> 27:21.103
YEAH, YOU HOOKED ME UP
WITH ONE GOOD PRODUCER,

27:21.103 --> 27:22.620
AND YOU GAVE ME A RIDE HOME
FROM THE HOSPITAL.

27:22.620 --> 27:24.275
THANKS!

27:24.275 --> 27:25.620
BUT HOW ABOUT YOUDON'T
PULL OUT THE CRAZY?

27:25.620 --> 27:29.448
MM. AND SO IT BEGINS.

27:29.448 --> 27:30.931
I HAVE HAD YOUR BACK
FROM DAY ONE,

27:30.931 --> 27:32.344
AND AS MUCH OF A JERK
AS WES IS,

27:32.344 --> 27:34.448
YOU'RE BEING
AN EVEN BIGGER ONE RIGHT NOW,

27:34.448 --> 27:35.551
AND IT'S REALLY WACK.

27:35.551 --> 27:37.482
I DON'T WANT TO FIGHT
WITH YOU, APRIL.

27:37.482 --> 27:39.034
I'M ABOUT TO HAVE
MY FIRST LIVE PERFORMANCE

27:39.034 --> 27:41.517
IN YEARS, AND MY FIRST
SOLO PERFORMANCE EVER.

27:41.517 --> 27:43.310
IF YOU CAN GET WES TO MOVE
AND COME UP WITH SOMETHING

27:43.310 --> 27:46.689
BETTER THAN A 360 DEAL,
I'LL BE OPEN TO HEARING IT.

27:46.689 --> 27:48.379
THAT'S THE BEST I CAN DO.

27:48.379 --> 27:51.482
ALL RIGHT, REED. WE'LL TALK
ABOUT THIS LATER. [ HUFFS ]

27:51.482 --> 27:53.206
I APOLOGIZE...

27:53.206 --> 27:55.034
IF I OWE YOU ONE.

27:55.034 --> 27:57.310
APOLOGY ACCEPTED...

27:57.310 --> 27:58.965
IF THAT WASONE.

28:08.275 --> 28:09.965
THANKS FOR THE HOOKUP, VAL.

28:09.965 --> 28:11.862
I'VE BEEN SO BUSY
SHOWING PROPERTIES,

28:11.862 --> 28:13.862
I HAVEN'T HAD TIME TO SHOP
FOR SOMETHING

28:13.862 --> 28:16.448
TO WEAR TO REED'S SHOW.

28:16.448 --> 28:20.172
WHAT ARE BEST FRIENDS FOR,
IF NOT TO GIVE YOU CLOTHES?

28:20.172 --> 28:21.172
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

28:21.172 --> 28:22.379
OH, NO.

28:22.379 --> 28:24.344
I'M PAYING YOU FOR THIS.

28:24.344 --> 28:25.931
WELL, MALCOLM IS.

28:25.931 --> 28:28.620
WHAT ARE BOYFRIENDS FOR
IF NOT TO BUY YOU CLOTHES?

28:28.620 --> 28:30.517
[ BOTH LAUGH ]I'LL RING HER UP, VAL.

28:30.517 --> 28:33.586
OMAR, I TOLD YOU YOU COULD LEAVE
A HALF AN HOUR AGO.

28:33.586 --> 28:36.586
USUALLY YOU'RE SPRINTING
OUT OF HERE TO GET TO DEREK.

28:36.586 --> 28:38.655
THAT WAS BEFORE
I REALIZED SOMETHING.

28:38.655 --> 28:40.034
WHAT?

28:40.034 --> 28:42.413
I DON'T LIKE DEREK VERY MUCH.WHY?

28:42.413 --> 28:45.034
OLD DEREK WAS SPONTANEOUS
AND FUN.

28:45.034 --> 28:47.068
NEW DEREK
SITS AROUND THE HOUSE

28:47.068 --> 28:49.413
PLAYING VIDEO GAMES
AND WATCHING TV.

28:49.413 --> 28:50.896
I'M OVER IT.

28:50.896 --> 28:53.758
[ HUFFS ] DAMN. THAT WAS QUICK.
IT HASN'T EVEN BEEN A WEEK.

28:53.758 --> 28:56.551
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO GET SICK
OF SOMEONE YOU LIKE UNTIL AFTER

28:56.551 --> 28:58.241
THE FIRST SIX MONTHS.YEAH.

28:58.241 --> 29:01.172
YOU HAVE TO GIVE YOURSELF TIME
TO ADJUST.

29:01.172 --> 29:03.793
LIVING WITH SOMEONE
CAN BE CHALLENGING.

29:03.793 --> 29:05.655
IT TOOK ME A WHILE
TO GET USED TO KEISHA.

29:05.655 --> 29:06.931
HA HA.

29:06.931 --> 29:08.896
BUT YOU'RE NOT SLEEPING
WITH KEISHA,

29:08.896 --> 29:10.862
AND IF DEREK WERE JUST
MY ROOMMATE,

29:10.862 --> 29:13.068
I'D BE FORCED TO ADJUST,
BUT WE'RE DATING,

29:13.068 --> 29:15.034
SO THIS SHOULD COME
MORE NATURALLY.

29:15.034 --> 29:17.931
WELL, HAVE YOU TRIED
TALKING TO HIM?NO.

29:17.931 --> 29:20.517
HOW DO YOU TELL SOMEONE
THAT WHEN YOU LOOK AT THEM,

29:20.517 --> 29:22.241
YOU GET IRRITATED?

29:22.241 --> 29:25.724
THE WAY HE WALKS,
THE WAY HE CHEWS?

29:25.724 --> 29:27.137
THE OTHER DAY, HE SNEEZED,

29:27.137 --> 29:29.931
AND I WAS SO IRRITATED,
I DIDN'T EVEN SAY "BLESS YOU."

29:29.931 --> 29:32.103
OH. THAT IS BAD.

29:32.103 --> 29:34.310
YOU HAVE BUYER'S REMORSE.

29:34.310 --> 29:36.413
I HAD A LITTLE BIT OF THAT
WITH VAL.

29:39.586 --> 29:41.896
I NEVER SAID ANYTHING BECAUSE
YOU'RE TOO SENSITIVE.

29:41.896 --> 29:44.827
♪♪♪

29:44.827 --> 29:47.758
SO...ARE YOU GONNA
KICK HIM OUT?

29:47.758 --> 29:51.275
WHEN HE DOESN'T HAVE A JOB?
NO, THAT'D JUST BE CRUEL.

29:51.275 --> 29:52.379
SO WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

29:52.379 --> 29:53.689
THE ONLY THING I CANDO.

29:53.689 --> 29:55.689
I'M GONNA BE COLD,
DISTANT, AND VAGUE

29:55.689 --> 29:57.103
SO HE'LL KICK HIMSELF OUT.

29:57.103 --> 29:59.931
MEN DO THAT TO WOMEN
ALL THE TIME.

29:59.931 --> 30:02.310
IT IS JUVENILE AND MEAN.

30:02.310 --> 30:04.896
WHY DO GUYS
ALWAYS DO THAT?

30:04.896 --> 30:06.862
BECAUSE IT WORKS.

30:06.862 --> 30:08.482
I WILL NEVER
UNDERSTAND BOYS.

30:08.482 --> 30:12.034
I'M LEAVING.
LOCK UP FOR ME, OKAY?

30:12.034 --> 30:13.379
YOU GOT IT.

30:13.379 --> 30:16.827
OH. I'LL WALK OUT WITH YOU.
BYE.

30:23.758 --> 30:25.517
YOU DIDN'T GET THE NICKNAME
"T.M.I."

30:25.517 --> 30:28.172
FOR STANDING AROUND,
SAYING NOTHING ALL DAY.

30:28.172 --> 30:32.379
MAKE ME FORGET MY PROBLEMS
BY TELLING ME YOURS.

30:32.379 --> 30:33.758
WHAT'S WRONG?

30:33.758 --> 30:35.448
GABE IS STUPID.

30:35.448 --> 30:38.896
YOU WANNA BE
MORE SPECIFIC?

30:40.620 --> 30:42.655
THE THREESOME.

30:42.655 --> 30:44.586
MM.

30:44.586 --> 30:47.068
I WAS SUPPOSED TO GO HIGH,
AND GABE WAS SUPPOSED TO GO LOW,

30:47.068 --> 30:49.034
AND THEN THEY ACTED LIKE
I WASN'T EVEN THERE.

30:49.034 --> 30:52.689
THEY DIDN'T EVEN NOTICE
WHEN I GOT UP AND LEFT.

30:52.689 --> 30:54.206
OUCH.

30:54.206 --> 30:56.206
SO LIKE I SAID,
HE'S STUPID.

30:56.206 --> 30:58.413
AND I'M NEVER
TALKING TO HIM AGAIN.

30:58.413 --> 31:00.793
HE WAS SO INTO HER.

31:00.793 --> 31:02.482
I'M SORRY.

31:02.482 --> 31:05.137
ANYWAY, I GOT ALL THE WAY
DOWN TO MY BLOCK,

31:05.137 --> 31:07.344
AND THEN I THOUGHT, LIKE,
WHAT AM I DOING?

31:07.344 --> 31:09.241
SEX IS SUPPOSED TO BE FUN.

31:09.241 --> 31:12.172
SO? DID YOU GO BACK
AND HAVE SOME FUN?

31:12.172 --> 31:13.517
HELL, NO.

31:13.517 --> 31:14.931
TOLD YOU.

31:14.931 --> 31:17.068
THREE'S A CROWD.

31:17.068 --> 31:20.931
WHY DO I EVEN CARE?YOU CARE BECAUSE YOU CARE.

31:20.931 --> 31:23.827
YOU'RE JUST HURT BECAUSE YOU
THINK YOU'RE NOT ENOUGH FOR HIM.

31:23.827 --> 31:25.586
OBVIOUSLY, I'M NOT ENOUGH
FOR HIM.

31:25.586 --> 31:27.655
YOU KNOW,
MAYBE I'M THE STUPID ONE

31:27.655 --> 31:30.655
FOR THINKING THAT HE EVEN
LIKED ME IN THE FIRST PLACE.

31:30.655 --> 31:33.862
THAT'S THE ONLY REASON
I DID THE THREESOME.

31:33.862 --> 31:35.413
WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU MADE IT SOUND

31:35.413 --> 31:37.724
LIKE YOU WERE EXPERIMENTING
JUST TO EXPERIMENT.

31:37.724 --> 31:41.413
DOES HE KNOW YOU DID IT
JUST BECAUSE YOU LIKE HIM?

31:41.413 --> 31:43.517
IDIDN'T EVEN KNOW THAT
I DID IT BECAUSE I LIKED HIM

31:43.517 --> 31:44.931
UNTIL RIGHT NOW.

31:44.931 --> 31:48.689
WELL...I THINK
YOU SHOULD TELL HIM.

31:50.724 --> 31:52.137
BUT WHATEVER YOU DO,

31:52.137 --> 31:54.724
DON'T INVITE HIM TO MOVE IN
WITH YOU.

31:54.724 --> 31:57.275
HE MIGHT SNEEZE.

32:00.448 --> 32:01.310
WATCH EPISODE COMMENTARY
FROM THE SHOW'S CREATOR

32:19.551 --> 32:23.137
OH. HELLO. [ CHUCKLES ]

32:23.137 --> 32:25.379
WELL, HELLO AGAIN,
AND SO SOON.

32:25.379 --> 32:27.137
AH.WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

32:27.137 --> 32:29.724
I'M, UH, LOOKING FOR MALCOLM,
ACTUALLY.

32:29.724 --> 32:31.206
HE'S NOT HERE.

32:31.206 --> 32:33.137
I'LL...WAIT,
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

32:33.137 --> 32:34.310
ACTUALLY, I DO MIND.

32:34.310 --> 32:36.655
I'M ON MY WAY OUT
TO MEET UP WITH HIM NOW.

32:36.655 --> 32:38.586
CAN I GIVE HIM A MESSAGE
FOR YOU?

32:38.586 --> 32:41.310
JUST TELL HIM
TO CHECK HIS VOICEMAIL.

32:43.379 --> 32:46.103
ON SECOND THOUGHT,
COME IN.

32:46.103 --> 32:49.172
ARE YOU SURE I'M NOT
HOLDING YOU UP?

32:52.034 --> 32:54.482
I THINK THIS IS WORTH
A FEW MORE MINUTES,

32:54.482 --> 32:57.724
BECAUSE I WANT EVERYTHING
TO REMAIN COOL BETWEEN US.

32:57.724 --> 32:59.931
OH, I WOULD LIKE THAT,
TOO.

32:59.931 --> 33:01.206
MM-HMM.

33:02.482 --> 33:07.275
I DON'T MIND THAT MALCOLM
IS PROTECTIVE OF YOU,

33:07.275 --> 33:09.413
EVEN THOUGH YOUR RELATIONSHIP
IS OVER AND HAS BEEN

33:09.413 --> 33:10.724
FOR QUITE SOME TIME.

33:10.724 --> 33:12.586
KEISHA...AND THE FACT THAT

33:12.586 --> 33:15.068
YOU STILL WANT MALCOLM
DOESN'T BOTHER ME EITHER,

33:15.068 --> 33:17.448
BECAUSE YOU'RE ENTITLED
TO FEEL YOUR FEELINGS,

33:17.448 --> 33:20.172
BUT THE MINUTE THEY START
GETTING IN MY WAY,

33:20.172 --> 33:22.344
THAT'S WHEN
WE'RE GONNA HAVE A PROBLEM.

33:22.344 --> 33:23.413
[ HUFFS ]

33:23.413 --> 33:24.931
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE THINKING.

33:24.931 --> 33:27.275
I JUST CAME BY TO GIVE MALCOLM
A SET OF SALON KEYS

33:27.275 --> 33:29.448
BEFORE I CATCH THE RED EYE
TO JAPAN.

33:29.448 --> 33:32.448
THIS IS ONLY ABOUT ME NEEDING
HIS HELP WITH TERRENCE.

33:32.448 --> 33:33.827
I HEAR WHAT YOU'RE SAYING,

33:33.827 --> 33:36.068
BUT I'M MORE FOCUSED
ON WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

33:36.068 --> 33:38.000
IN THE COURSE OF TWO DAYS,

33:38.000 --> 33:40.724
YOU'VE STOPPED BY UNEXPECTEDLY
TWO TIMES.

33:40.724 --> 33:42.310
NOW A MAN MIGHT BELIEVE

33:42.310 --> 33:45.482
THAT IT'S JUST ABOUT HIS BROTHER
AND YOUR SALON,

33:45.482 --> 33:46.896
BUT I'M A WOMAN.

33:46.896 --> 33:48.448
I KNOW HOW WE DO.

33:48.448 --> 33:51.965
I APOLOGIZE IF I HAVE MADE YOU
QUESTION THE NATURE

33:51.965 --> 33:54.827
OF MY MOTIVES
WHERE MALCOLM'S CONCERNED.

33:54.827 --> 33:56.241
I DIDN'T NEED AN APOLOGY.

33:56.241 --> 33:58.310
I JUST NEEDED
TO MAKE MYSELF CLEAR.

33:58.310 --> 33:59.793
AND I THINK I'VE DONE THAT.

33:59.793 --> 34:01.448
YOU HAVE.

34:03.655 --> 34:06.034
ASHLEE?

34:06.034 --> 34:08.275
DON'T YOU WANNA LEAVE
THE KEYS?

34:08.275 --> 34:12.413
I MEAN, ISN'T THAT THE REASON
YOU STOPPED BY?

34:18.689 --> 34:20.965
[ FOOTSTEPS DEPART ]

34:23.965 --> 34:26.034
♪♪♪

34:26.034 --> 34:27.344
OH!

34:27.344 --> 34:28.758
I CAN'T BELIEVE
SHE HAD THE NERVE

34:28.758 --> 34:30.620
TO SHOW UP UNANNOUNCED AGAIN.

34:30.620 --> 34:32.000
WHAT DID MALCOLM SAY?

34:32.000 --> 34:34.448
HE JUST ASKED IF I COOL,
AND I SAID I WAS.

34:34.448 --> 34:37.137
WHAT I DIDN'T TELL HIM
IS THAT I DON'T LIKE HER,

34:37.137 --> 34:38.448
AND I DON'T TRUST HER.

34:38.448 --> 34:40.310
BUT AT LEAST SHE KNOWS
I GOT HER NUMBER.

34:40.310 --> 34:41.448
I WANNA HEAR THE REST,

34:41.448 --> 34:43.310
BUT I GOTTA GET THIS THING
STARTED.

34:43.310 --> 34:44.655
DO YOUR THING, GIRL.

34:44.655 --> 34:46.413
WE'RE ROOTING FOR YOU.
GOOD LUCK.

34:46.413 --> 34:47.655
THANK YOU.

34:47.655 --> 34:52.724
♪♪♪

34:52.724 --> 34:54.482
HEY, IT'S YOU.

34:54.482 --> 34:58.793
♪♪♪

34:58.793 --> 35:00.931
[ Amplified voice ]
GOOD EVENING, ATLANTA.

35:00.931 --> 35:02.103
I'M MR. BANGLADESH,

35:02.103 --> 35:04.068
AND IF I COULD HAVE
YOUR UNDIVIDED ATTENTION

35:04.068 --> 35:06.068
FOR A MOMENT, PLEASE,

35:06.068 --> 35:09.620
AS YOU ALL KNOW, WE ARE HERE
TO LISTEN TO REED DURHAM

35:09.620 --> 35:11.482
PERFORM TONIGHT.

35:11.482 --> 35:14.068
I'VE KNOWN REED EVER SINCE
HE WAS IN N.R.G.

35:14.068 --> 35:16.655
DOING THOSE CORNY-ASS
DANCE STEPS.

35:16.655 --> 35:18.551
ONE THING I LEARNED THEN

35:18.551 --> 35:20.724
WHICH YOU'RE ALL GONNA LEARN
TODAY --

35:20.724 --> 35:22.137
THIS WHITE BOY GOT SWAG.

35:22.137 --> 35:24.344
EVERYONE, GIVE IT UP
FOR REED DURHAM.

35:24.344 --> 35:28.482
[ CHEERING ]

35:28.482 --> 35:31.034
♪ TOO YOUNG, TOO BOLD ♪

35:31.034 --> 35:32.793
♪ NO MORE SINGING IN THE MALL ♪

35:32.793 --> 35:35.034
♪ AIN'T THIS WHAT I DREAMED? ♪

35:35.034 --> 35:36.931
♪ WELL,
THAT'S HOW IT STARTED OUT ♪

35:36.931 --> 35:38.586
♪ OH, OH ♪

35:38.586 --> 35:41.137
♪ GIRL, THAT'S HOW
IT STARTED OUT ♪

35:41.137 --> 35:43.862
♪ OH, OH ♪

35:43.862 --> 35:45.034
♪♪♪

35:45.034 --> 35:47.655
♪ WELCOME, YOU'LL SEE ♪

35:47.655 --> 35:49.275
♪ LIVE OUT EVERY FANTASY ♪

35:49.275 --> 35:51.655
♪ EVERYONE HAS ONE ♪

35:51.655 --> 35:53.379
♪ EVEN THE BROKENHEARTED ♪

35:53.379 --> 35:55.275
♪ OH, OH ♪

35:55.275 --> 35:58.758
HELLO?♪ EVEN THE BROKENHEARTED,
OH, OH ♪

35:58.758 --> 36:00.724
YEAH.

36:00.724 --> 36:02.551
YEAH, I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

36:02.551 --> 36:04.310
[ CELL PHONE CLATTERS ]

36:04.310 --> 36:05.517
WHAT HAPPENED?

36:05.517 --> 36:08.482
TERRENCE JUST GOT ARRESTED
AT ASHLEE'S SALON.

36:08.482 --> 36:10.482
I HAVE TO GO TAKE CARE
OF THIS RIGHT NOW.

36:10.482 --> 36:13.068
I'M SORRY.NO. OF COURSE.

36:13.068 --> 36:15.103
SHOULD I COME WITH YOU?

36:15.103 --> 36:16.379
NO, BABE. I GOT THIS.

36:16.379 --> 36:18.034
♪ SLOWLY START TO FALL ♪

36:18.034 --> 36:20.103
♪ I CAN'T LOOK IN YOUR EYES ♪

36:20.103 --> 36:21.517
[ MOUTHS WORD ]

36:21.517 --> 36:23.379
♪ I'M LOST IN IT ALL ♪

36:23.379 --> 36:25.241
♪♪♪

36:25.241 --> 36:28.586
♪ I'M LOST IN IT ALL ♪

36:28.586 --> 36:30.103
♪♪♪

36:30.103 --> 36:33.241
SO, OMAR, I'M CURIOUS.

36:33.241 --> 36:34.586
HAVE YOU EVER BEEN
WITH A GIRL?

36:34.586 --> 36:38.241
YEP.YEAH?

36:38.241 --> 36:39.482
ANDREA BROWN.

36:39.482 --> 36:42.896
WE GOT TOGETHER AT RECESS
IN FOURTH GRADE.

36:42.896 --> 36:44.482
BY THE TIME THE BELL RANG
AT 3:00,

36:44.482 --> 36:46.068
WE WERE BROKEN UP.

36:46.068 --> 36:47.206
WHAT HAPPENED?

36:47.206 --> 36:48.827
BITCH WANTED HER STICKERS BACK.

36:48.827 --> 36:50.000
